A contender for the Office of Speaker of the 9th House of Representatives, Rt. Hon. John Dyegh, yesterday felicitated with the Muslim Umma and Nigerians generally as they begin the month-long Ramadan fast. A statement from the Dyegh Campaign Organisation (DCC), made available to the media in Abuja, appealed to Nigerians to pray for peace, justice, equality and harmony in the nation, adding that “Ramadan is a time for charity, reflection and sacrifice.” Dyegh, according to the statement, described “Islam as a religion of peace whose adherents practice true love and religious harmony; seek mutual coexistence, and pursue positive development of human kind.